9 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why LA Should Be Nerfed!</span><hr size=1> It's plain and simple, left axe does way too much damage compared to the rest of the game. This is why...<br>
<br>
On a pure damage to damage, damage to armor ratio, LA does 52.5% more damage per round then the next highest damage melee class.<br>
<br>
Damage to Damage<br>
Berserker: (50LA-50Hammer)<br>
Damage Per Round: 125% + 100% / 2 = 112.5% * 1.2 (20%) = 135% * 1.5 (50%) = 202.5%.<br>
(Assuming LA is only 100%)<br>
Mercenary: (50DW-50Crush)<br>
Damage Per Round: 100% * 1.5 = 150%.<br>
<br>
202.5% - 150% = 52.5% more left axe damge per round.<br>
<br>
All things being equal, equal hps, no styles, no class-specific skills, no RA's, 52.5% more damage per round is tremendious.<br>
<br>
Damage to Armor<br>
Berserker: (Cloth armor)<br>
Absorb Per Round: 0%<br>
Mercenary: (Plate armor)<br>
Absorb Per Round: 34%<br>
<br>
52.5% - 34% = 18.5% more damage per round.<br>
<br>
In a straight up fight all things being equal, a berserker in cloth will do 18.5% more damage per round than a mercenary in plate!<br>
<br>
Please remember this isn't a comparision of a mercenary versus a berserker, this is left axe versus the next highest melee damage class.<br>
<br>
LA versus the next highest two-handed damage class.<br>
Berserker: (50LA-50Hammer)<br>
Damage Per Round: 125% + 100% / 2 = 112.5% * 1.2 (20%) = 135% * 1.5 (50%) = 202.5%.<br>
(Assuming LA is only 100%)<br>
Absorb Per Round: 0% (Cloth)<br>
Armsman: (50Pole-50Crush)<br>
Damage Per Round: 100% + 100% + 15% = 215%.<br>
Absorb Per Round: 34% (Plate)<br>
<br>
LA is roughly twice as fast as pole per round.<br>
202.5% * 2 = 406% - 215% = 190%<br>
190% - 34% = 156% more damage per round.<br>
<br>
In a straight up fight all things being equal, a berserker in cloth will do 156% more damage per round than the next highest two-handed damage class! In cloth...<br>
<br>
Obviously there are tons of factors that seperate the classes such as styles, class-specific skills etc. But all things being even (/laughs at zerkers in cloth being even) those are the damage ratios.<br>
<br>
Most of the formulas for LA damage include some type of skill division by two for a % bonus to damage. That is obviously not the formula Mythic is using to determine LA damage. If you do divide the LA skill by two for a % bonus, things begin to even out.<br>
<br>
Berserker: (50LA-50Hammer)<br>
Damage Per Round: 125% + 100% / 2 = 112.5 * 1.2 (20%) = 135% * 1.25 (50/2%) = 168.75%.<br>
(Assuming LA is only 100%)<br>
Absorb Per Round: 19%<br>
Mercenary: (50DW-50Crush)<br>
Damage Per Round: 100% * 1.5 = 150%<br>
Absorb Per Round: 27%<br>
<br>
168.75% - 150% = 18.75% more left axe damage per round.<br>
27% - 19% = 8% more chain absorb.<br>
18.75% - 8% = 10.75% more left axe damage per round.<br>
<br>
Given styles, different armor types, class-specific skills, and more, 10.75% damage difference is much more realistic than 52.5%!  Not dividing the LA skill by 2 for bonus %, is similar to allowing mercenaries 100% chance to dual wield.<br>
<br>
Please look into the LA damage formula in relation to the rest of the classes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#000000>(1/29/03 11:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why LA Should Be Nerfed!</span><hr size=1> Too much damage? /boggle<br>
