<br>
You obviously don't even understand how left axe works.  Its very clear you don't play a zerk on a regular basis if at all.<br>
<br>
<br>
Left Axe is completly different from every other skill in the game.  By placing an axe in the left hand spot you automaticaly reduce the damage by 50%.<br>
<br>
The current formula seems to be base damage as follows:<br>
Right Hand base damage:  50% + 10% (left axe base bonus from a few patches ago) + spec/2 (at 50 spec = 85% base damage of a normal 1 handed weapon)<br>
<br>
Left Hand base damage: 50% + 10% (as above) = 60% normal 1 handed damage.<br>
<br>
Ok, now look its equal to a 2handed weapon in function. (can't use a shield while doing either).  <br>
2handed base damage in Midgard is 115-140% (depending on tests) base damage of the equivalent 1handed while in Albion and Hibernia is 140-150%.  Thats base damage unspecced before styles.  In order for left axe to equal that... a zerk has to spec fully in left axe to 50.  To equal base damage of an unspecced 2handed weapon in the other realms.<br>
<br>
No factor in that although both weapons SWING each round, the left axe swings with no bonus or to hit increase.  Thus misses and gets evaded/parried/blocked much more often. (not to mention most zerks use a fast axe in left hand to benefit from the haste effect) bringing the base damage down to 85%. <br>
<br>
