<br>
I hit you for 100 damage while your wearing cloth.<br>
You hit me for 150 damage while I'm wearing plate.<br>
<br>
You hit me for 50% more damage difference.  (In essence 50% more damage per round.)<br>
<br>
I hit you for 100 damage while your wearing cloth.<br>
You hit me for 200 damage while I'm wearing cloth.<br>
<br>
You hit me for 100% damage difference.  (In essence 100% more damage per round.)<br>
<br>
It's to show that even while I have cloth armor on, and you have plate armor on, you still have a higher percent damage ratio on top of our absorb.  I probably should of worded it damage difference to make it more clear.  Regardless, I'll think of a new way to post the damage difference between LA and DW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=connorrowynsun>Connor Rowynsun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#000000>(1/31/03 10:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why LA Should Be Nerfed!</span><hr size=1> Setting aside the fact that you've come here and cried for nerf, it would be helpful if you explained how you arrived at the following formulas:<br>
<br>
Damage to Damage<br>
Berserker: (50LA-50Hammer)<br>
Damage Per Round: 125% + 100% / 2 = 112.5% * 1.2 (20%) = 135% * 1.5 (50%) = 202.5%.<br>
(Assuming LA is only 100%)<br>
Mercenary: (50DW-50Crush)<br>
Damage Per Round: 100% * 1.5 = 150%.<br>
<br>
202.5% - 150% = 52.5% more left axe damge per round.<br>
 <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.1 Berserker<br>
