The current formula seems to be base damage as follows:<br>
Right Hand base damage: 50% + 10% (left axe base bonus from a few patches ago) + spec/2 (at 50 spec = 85% base damage of a normal 1 handed weapon)<br>
<br>
Left Hand base damage: 50% + 10% (as above) = 60% normal 1 handed damage.<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Are you sure your left hand base damage doesn't increase like your right hand damage?<br>
<br>
The reason why it may look like you describe is because many Berserkers use a 15 DPS Hand Axe in their off-hand to maximize their haste.  Berserkers main damage lies in the LA Style bonus regardless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kethryndc>Kethryn DC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#000000>(1/31/03 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why LA Should Be Nerfed!</span><hr size=1> Aye, left hand base damage does not scale as you increase in left axe spec from all the testing that I have done.  Get 2 zerks both the same level, one with say 40 left axe, another with 50.  Using the same left axe (and everything else being equal) they will hit with the offhand for the same amount.<br>
