<br>
85% base x100% of DW= 160-175-ish% of the base damage of any 1H person<br>
<br>
62.5%DW chance x100% base damage= same.<br>
<br>
The document we all read made ti very clear that Mythic originally set up these odd figures in order to make both parties have the sama damage.<br>
<br>
The zerker does, however, receive greater effects from the Haste Effect and damage adds (because his offhand hits 100% time)<br>
<br>
The styles for LA are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> over twice </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as great as those for CDW, yet their base damage is the same.<br>
<br>
The myth that unstyled LA damage is absolutely nerfed is a myth- its the same as CDW, effectively.<br>
<br>
The zerkers style bonuses overcompensated for their weak defense, something the merc and BM will never experience. Mythic is scared to offend the zerk players by reducing their styles by the original 40% nerf, and seems to have settles for a 25%-ish nerf on a class that is notorious for 2-shotting full melee classes. <p>Blame<br>
