<br>
Me left hand using 2 MP cleavers does far less damage unstyled each hit then my right hand does.<br>
<br>
right Hand base damage is 85% of full on right hand.  If specced to 50 Left Axe, left hand is 60 or 65% (forget exactly) of Base.  <br>
<br>
CD/DW do more unstyled damage then left axe.  Thats why Left was given a slight boost in base damage around 1.58 I believe.  Because lack of endurance meant they were hitting at about healer damage with both weapons combined.  Before that patch I'd hit unstyled on yellow cons for combined damage of somewhere between 50 and 60 if I was lucky.  After I may hit 100.  (Mobs not players, unstyled on players is considerable less if they have good resists)<br>
<br>
Wyrd's growth factor doesn't take into account the lower base damage.  PERIOD.<br>
<br>
Its that base damage that figures style damage.  If you have a weapon that does 100 base damage and apply a style that does 50% its going to do 150.<br>
<br>
If you have a weapon that does 75% of that base damage and use the same style you're only going to 137.5 damage.  But if you increase that style to 100%, bam, you do 150 damage.  Same damage, different style percents.<br>
<br>
You look and see a zerk hit for 400.  Ask yourself, what weapons are you using?  What is he using?  He's normally using a 4.0 or greater dealy weapon in right hand, has 60 or lower quick and no haste effects.  From what I've seen posted here and elsewhere, Mercs and BMs are using 3.0 and lower delay weapons, have capped quick and are using haste effects.  <br>
<br>
Its apples and oranges.  the zerk is going to hit harder per hit. The Merc and BM are going to hit more often.  (yes, I do know that CD/DW needed a boost to equal zerk damage prior to 1.62 but thats how it was working). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ulfhednar1>Ulfhednar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#000000>(5/16/03 11:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: growth factors</span><hr size=1> &quot;The zerkers style bonuses overcompensated for their weak defense, something the merc and BM will never experience. Mythic is scared to offend the zerk players by reducing their styles by the original 40% nerf, and seems to have settles for a 25%-ish nerf on a class that is notorious for 2-shotting full melee classes&quot;<br>
